  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key components typically include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Customer identification and verification requirements\n3. Record-keeping obligations\n4. Screening for potential money laundering activities\n5. Reporting large cash transactions\n6. Implementing compliance programs\n7. Imposing penalties for non-compliance\n\nDifferent countries have their own specific AML laws, but many follow international standards set by organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF).",
